1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,700
١ ألف لام را
1. Alif-Lam-Ra.

2
00:00:04,700 --> 00:00:08,980
تلك آيات الكتاب المبين
These are the verses of the clear Book.

3
00:00:08,980 --> 00:00:16,740
٢ إنا أنزلناه قرآنا عربيا لعلكم تعقلون
2. Indeed, We have sent it down as an Arabic Quran so that you may understand.

4
00:00:16,740 --> 00:00:24,320
٣ نحن نقص عليك أحسن القصص بما أوحينا إليك هذا القرآن
3. We relate to you ˹O Prophet˺ the best of stories through Our revelation of this Quran,

5
00:00:24,320 --> 00:00:32,980
وإن كنت من قبله لمن الغافلين
though before this you were totally unaware ˹of them˺.

6
00:00:32,980 --> 00:00:40,520
٤ إذ قال يوسف لأبيه يا أبت إني رأيت أحد عشر كوكبا
4. ˹Remember˺ when Joseph said to his father, "O my dear father! Indeed I dreamt of eleven stars,

7
00:00:40,520 --> 00:00:45,220
والشمس والقمر رأيتهم لي ساجدين
and the sun, and the moon—I saw them prostrating to me!"

8
00:00:45,220 --> 00:00:52,660
٥ قال يا بني لا تقصص رؤياك على إخوتك فيكيدوا لك كيدا
5. He replied, "O my dear son! Do not relate your vision to your brothers, or they will devise a plot against you.

9
00:00:52,660 --> 00:00:59,220
إن الشيطان للإنسان عدو مبين
Surely Satan is a sworn enemy to humankind.

10
00:00:59,220 --> 00:01:06,940
٦ وكذلك يجتبيك ربك ويعلمك من تأويل الأحاديث
6. And so will your Lord choose you ˹O Joseph˺, and teach you the interpretation of dreams,

11
00:01:06,940 --> 00:01:16,940
ويتم نعمته عليك وعلى آل يعقوب كما أتمها على أبويك من قبل
and perfect His favour upon you and the descendants of Jacob—˹just˺ as He once perfected it upon your forefathers,

12
00:01:16,940 --> 00:01:24,180
كما أتمها على أبويك من قبل إبراهيم وإسحاق
of Jacob—˹just˺ as He once perfected it upon your forefathers, Abraham and Isaac.

13
00:01:24,180 --> 00:01:28,420
إن ربك عليم حكيم
Surely your Lord is All-Knowing, All-Wise."

14
00:01:28,420 --> 00:01:37,240
٧ لقد كان في يوسف وإخوته آيات للسائلين
7. Indeed, in the story of Joseph and his brothers there are lessons for all who ask.

15
00:01:37,240 --> 00:01:44,280
٨ إذ قالوا ليوسف وأخوه أحب إلى أبينا منا ونحن عصبة
8. ˹Remember˺ when they said ˹to one another˺, "Surely Joseph and his brother ˹Benjamin˺ are more beloved to our father than we, even though we are a group of so many.

16
00:01:44,280 --> 00:01:48,880
إن أبانا لفي ضلال مبين
Indeed, our father is clearly mistaken.

17
00:01:48,880 --> 00:01:55,340
٩ أقتلوا يوسف أو اطرحوه أرضا يخل لكم وجه أبيكم
9. Kill Joseph or cast him out to some ˹distant˺ land so that our father's attention will be only ours,

18
00:01:55,340 --> 00:02:01,100
وتكونوا من بعده قوما صالحين
then after that you may ˹repent and˺ become righteous people!"

19
00:02:01,100 --> 00:02:09,220
١٠ قال قائل منهم لا تقتلوا يوسف وألقوه في غيابة الجب
10. One of them said, "Do not kill Joseph. But if you must do something, throw him into the bottom of a well

20
00:02:09,220 --> 00:02:18,260
يلتقطه بعض السيارة إن كنتم فاعلين
so perhaps he may be picked up by some travellers."

21
00:02:18,260 --> 00:02:27,560
١١ قالوا يا أبانا ما لك لا تأمنا على يوسف وإنا له لناصحون
11. They said, "O our father! Why do you not trust us with Joseph, although we truly wish him well?

22
00:02:27,560 --> 00:02:35,020
١٢ أرسله معنا غدا يرتع ويلعب وإنا له لحافظون
12. Send him out with us tomorrow so that he may enjoy himself and play. And we will really watch over him."

23
00:02:35,020 --> 00:02:45,900
١٣ قال إني ليحزنني أن تذهبوا به وأخاف أن يأكله الذئب وأنتم عنه غافلون
13. He responded, "It would truly sadden me if you took him away with you, and I fear that a wolf may devour him while you are negligent of him."

24
00:02:45,900 --> 00:02:54,160
١٤ قالوا لئن أكله الذئب ونحن عصبة إنا إذا لخاسرون
14. They said, "If a wolf were to devour him, despite our strong group, then we would certainly be losers!"

25
00:02:54,160 --> 00:03:01,400
١٥ فلما ذهبوا به وأجمعوا أن يجعلوه في غيابة الجب
15. And so, when they took him away and decided to throw him into the bottom of the well,

26
00:03:01,400 --> 00:03:09,860
وأوحينا إليه لتنبئنهم بأمرهم هذا وهم لا يشعرون
We inspired him: "˹One day˺ you will remind them of this deed of theirs while they are unaware ˹of who you are˺."

27
00:03:09,860 --> 00:03:16,620
١٦ وجاءوا أباهم عشاء يبكون
16. Then they returned to their father in the evening, weeping.

28
00:03:16,620 --> 00:03:26,680
١٧ قالوا يا أبانا إنا ذهبنا نستبق وتركنا يوسف عند متاعنا فأكله الذئب
17. They cried, "Our father! We went racing and left Joseph with our belongings, and a wolf devoured him!

29
00:03:26,680 --> 00:03:33,080
وما أنت بمؤمن لنا ولو كنا صادقين
But you will not believe us, no matter how truthful we are."

30
00:03:33,080 --> 00:03:46,680
١٨ وجاءوا على طميصه بدم كذب قال بل سولتنكم أنفسكم أمرا فصبر جميل
18. And they brought his shirt, stained with false blood. He responded, "No! Your souls must have tempted you to do something ˹evil˺. So ˹I can only endure with˺ beautiful patience!

31
00:03:46,680 --> 00:03:51,420
والله المستعان على ما تصفون
It is Allah's help that I seek to bear your claims."

32
00:03:51,420 --> 00:04:02,500
١٩ وجاءت سيارة فأرسلوا واردهم فأدلى دلوه قال يا بشرى هذا غلام
19. And there came some travellers, and they sent their water-boy who let down his bucket into the well. He cried out, "Oh, what a great find! Here is a boy!"

33
00:04:02,500 --> 00:04:09,160
وأسروه بضاعة والله عليم بما يعملون
And they took him secretly ˹to be sold˺ as merchandise, but Allah is All-Knowing of what they did.

34
00:04:09,160 --> 00:04:18,080
٢٠ وشروه بثمن بخص دراهم معدودة وكانوا فيه من الزاهدين
20. They ˹later˺ sold him for a cheap price, just a few silver coins—only wanting to get rid of him.

35
00:04:18,080 --> 00:04:28,780
٢١ وقال الذي اشتراه من مصر لمرأته أكرمي مثواه عسى أن ينفعنا أو نتخذه ولدا
21. The man from Egypt who bought him said to his wife, "Take good care of him, perhaps he may be useful to us or we may adopt him as a son."

36
00:04:28,780 --> 00:04:37,700
وكذلك مكنا ليوسف في الأرض ولنعلمه من تأويل الأحاديث
This is how We established Joseph in the land, so that We might teach him the interpretation of dreams.

37
00:04:37,700 --> 00:04:46,360
والله غالب على أمره ولكن أكثر الناس لا يعلمون
Allah's Will always prevails, but most people do not know.

38
00:04:46,360 --> 00:04:55,480
٢٢ ولما بلغ أشده آتيناه حكما وعلما وكذلك نجزي المحسنين
22. And when he reached maturity, We gave him wisdom and knowledge. This is how We reward the good-doers.

39
00:04:55,480 --> 00:05:04,360
٢٣ وراودته التي هو في بيتها عن نفسه وغلقت الأبواب وقالت هيت لك
23. And the lady, in whose house he lived, tried to seduce him. She locked the doors ˹firmly˺ and said, "Come to me!" He replied, "Allah is my refuge!

40
00:05:04,360 --> 00:05:13,020
قال معاذ الله إنه ربي أحسن مثوايا إنه لا يفلح الظالمون
It is ˹not right to betray˺ my master, who has taken good care of me. Indeed, the wrongdoers never succeed."

41
00:05:13,020 --> 00:05:32,020
٢٤ ولقد همت به وهم بها لولا أرآ برهان ربه كذلك لنصرف عنه السوء والفحشاء إنه من عبادنا المخلصين
24. She advanced towards him, and he would have done likewise, had he not seen a sign from his Lord. This is how We kept evil and indecency away from him, for he was truly one of Our chosen servants.

42
00:05:32,020 --> 00:05:40,680
٢٥ واستبق الباب وقدت قميصه من دبر وألف يا سيدها لدى الباب
25. They raced for the door and she tore his shirt from the back, only to find her husband at the door.

43
00:05:40,680 --> 00:05:50,680
قالت ما جزاء من أراد بأهلك سوءا إلا أن يسجن أو عذاب أليم
She cried, "What is the penalty for someone who tried to violate your wife, except imprisonment or a painful punishment?"

44
00:05:50,680 --> 00:06:05,900
٢٦ قال هي راودتني عن نفسي وشهد شاهد من أهلها إن كان قميصه قد من قبل فصدقت وهو من الكاذبين
26. Joseph responded, "It was she who tried to seduce me." And a witness from her own family testified: "If his shirt is torn from the front, then she has told the truth and he is a liar.

45
00:06:05,900 --> 00:06:13,920
٢٧ وإن كان قميصه قد من دبر فكذبت وهو من الصادقين
27. But if it is torn from the back, then she has lied and he is truthful."

46
00:06:13,920 --> 00:06:27,080
٢٨ فلما رأى قميصه قد من دبر قال إنه من كيدكن عظيم
28. So when her husband saw that Joseph's shirt was torn from the back, he said ˹to her˺, "This must be ˹an example˺ of the cunning of you ˹women˺! Indeed, your cunning is so shrewd!

47
00:06:27,080 --> 00:06:36,680
٢٩ يوسف أعرض عن هذا واستغفرين ذنبك إنك كنت من الخاطئين
29. O Joseph! Forget about this. And you ˹O wife˺! Seek forgiveness for your sin. It certainly has been your fault."

48
00:06:36,680 --> 00:06:47,020
٣٠ وقال نسوة في المدينة امرأة العزيز تراود فتاها عن نفسه قد شغفها حبا
30. Some women of the city gossiped, "The Chief Minister's wife is trying to seduce her slave-boy. Love for him has plagued her heart.

49
00:06:47,020 --> 00:06:51,680
إنا لنراها في ضلال مبين
Some women of the city gossiped, "The Chief Minister's wife is trying to seduce her slave-boy. Love for him has plagued her heart. Indeed, we see that she is clearly mistaken."

50
00:06:51,680 --> 00:07:07,680
٣١ فلما سمعت بمكرهن أرسلت إليهن وأعتدت لهن متكأا وآتت كل واحدة منهن سكينا وقالت خرج عليهم
31. When she heard about their gossip, she invited them and set a banquet for them. She gave each one a knife, then said to Joseph, "Come out before them." When they saw him,

51
00:07:07,680 --> 00:07:21,960
فلما رأينه أكبرنه وقطعن أيديهن وقلن حاش لله ما هذا بشرا إن هذا إلا ملك كريم
they were so stunned ˹by his beauty˺ that they cut their hands, and exclaimed, "Good God! This cannot be human; this must be a noble angel!"

52
00:07:21,960 --> 00:07:31,420
٣٢ قالت فذلكن الذي لمتنني فيه ولقد راوته عن نفسه فاستعصم
32. She said, "This is the one for whose love you criticized me! I did try to seduce him but he ˹firmly˺ refused.

53
00:07:31,420 --> 00:07:39,200
ولئن لم يفعل ما آمره ليسجنن وليكون من الصاغرين
And if he does not do what I order him to, he will certainly be imprisoned and ˹fully˺ disgraced."

54
00:07:39,200 --> 00:07:52,660
٣٣ قال رب السجن أحب إلي مما يدعونني إليه وإلا تصرف عني كيدهن أصب إليهن وأكون من الجاهلين
33. He said, "My Lord, prison is more to my liking than that to which they invite me. And if You do not avert from me their plan, I might incline toward them and ˹thus˺ be of the ignorant."

55
00:07:52,660 --> 00:08:00,620
٣٤ فاستجاب له ربه فصرف عنه كيدهن إنه هو السميع العليم
34. So his Lord responded to him, turning their cunning away from him. Surely He is the All-Hearing, All-Knowing.

56
00:08:00,620 --> 00:08:08,800
٣٥ ثم بدى لهم من بعد ما رأوا الآيات ليسجننه حتى حين
35. And so it occurred to those in charge, despite seeing all the proofs ˹of his innocence˺, that he should be imprisoned for a while.

57
00:08:08,800 --> 00:08:16,160
٣٦ ودخل معه السجن فتيان قال أحدهما إني أراني أعصر خمرا
36. And two other servants went to jail with Joseph. One of them said, "I dreamt I was pressing wine." The other said,

58
00:08:16,160 --> 00:08:23,980
وقال الآخر إني أراني أحمل فوق رأسي خبزا تأكل الطير منه
"I dreamt I was carrying ˹some˺ bread on my head, from which birds were eating." ˹Then both said,˺ "Tell us their interpretation,

59
00:08:23,980 --> 00:08:29,820
نبئنا بتأويله إنا نراك من المحسنين
for we surely see you as one of the good-doers."

60
00:08:29,820 --> 00:08:44,240
٣٧ قال لا يأتيكما طعام ترزقانه إلا نبأتكما بتأويله قبل أن يأتيكما ذلكما مما علمني ربي
37. Joseph replied, "I can even tell you what kind of meal you will be served before you receive it. This ˹knowledge˺ is from what my Lord has taught me.

61
00:08:44,240 --> 00:08:53,220
إني تركت ملة قوم لا يؤمنون بالله وهم بالآخرة هم كافرون
I have shunned the faith of a people who disbelieve in Allah and deny the Hereafter.

62
00:08:53,220 --> 00:09:00,660
٣٨ واتبعت ملة آبائي إبراهيم وإسحاق ويعقوب
38. I follow the faith of my fathers: Abraham, Isaac,

63
00:09:00,660 --> 00:09:10,900
ما كان لنا أن نشرك بالله من شيء ذلك من فضل الله علينا وعلى الناس
and Jacob. It is not ˹right˺ for us to associate anything with Allah ˹in worship˺. This is part of Allah's grace upon us and humanity,

64
00:09:10,900 --> 00:09:15,620
ولكن أكثر الناس لا يشترون
but most people are not grateful.

65
00:09:15,620 --> 00:09:24,680
٣٩ يا صاحبي السجن أأرباب متفرقون خير أم الله الواحد القهار
39. O my fellow-prisoners! Which is far better: many different lords or Allah—the One, the Supreme?

66
00:09:24,680 --> 00:09:44,400
٤٠ ما تعبدون من دونه إلا أسماء سميتموها أنتم وآباؤكم ما أنزل الله بها من سلطان
40. Whatever ˹idols˺ you worship instead of Him are mere names which you and your forefathers have made up—a practice Allah has never authorized.

67
00:09:44,400 --> 00:09:57,500
إن الحكم إلا لله أمر أن لا تعبدوا إلا إياه ذلك الدين القيم ولكن أكثر الناس لا يعلمون
It is only Allah Who decides. He has commanded that you worship none but Him. That is the upright faith, but most people do not know.

68
00:09:57,500 --> 00:10:03,840
٤١ يا صاحبي السجن أما أحدكما فيسقي ربه خمرا
41. "O my fellow-prisoners! ˹The first˺ one of you will serve wine to his master,

69
00:10:03,840 --> 00:10:13,200
وأما الآخر فيسلب فتأكل الطير من رأسه قضي الأمر الذي فيه تستفتيان
and the other will be crucified and the birds will eat from his head. The matter about which you inquired has been decided."

70
00:10:13,200 --> 00:10:28,460
٤٢ وقال للذي ظن أنه ناج منهم اذكرني عند ربك فأنساه الشيطان ذكر ربه فلبث في السجن بطع سنين
42. Then he said to the one he knew would survive, "Mention me in the presence of your master." But Satan made him forget to mention Joseph to his master, so he remained in prison for several years.

71
00:10:28,460 --> 00:10:37,260
٤٣ وقال الملك إني أرى سبع بقرات سمان يأكلهن سبع عجاف
43. And ˹one day˺ the King said, "I dreamt of seven fat cows eaten up by seven skinny ones;

72
00:10:37,260 --> 00:10:42,380
وسبع سنبلات خضر وأخر يابسات
and seven green ears of grain and ˹seven˺ others dry.

73
00:10:42,380 --> 00:10:50,120
يا أيها الملأ أفتوني في رؤياي إن كنتم للرؤيا تعبرون
O chiefs! Tell me the meaning of my dream if you can interpret dreams."

74
00:10:50,120 --> 00:10:57,100
٤٤ قالوا أضغاث أحلام وما نحن بتأويل الأحلام بعالمين
44. They replied, "These are confused visions and we do not know the interpretation of such dreams."

75
00:10:57,100 --> 00:11:06,540
٤٥ وقال الذين جاء منهما وادكر بعد أمة أنا أنبئكم بتأويله فأرسنون
45. ˹Finally,˺ the surviving ex-prisoner remembered ˹Joseph˺ after a long time and said, "I will tell you its interpretation, so send me forth ˹to Joseph˺."

76
00:11:06,540 --> 00:11:15,420
٤٦ يوسف أيها الصديق أفتنا في سبع بقرات سمان يأكلهن سبع عجاف
46. ˹He said,˺ "Joseph, O man of truth! Interpret for us ˹the dream of˺ seven fat cows eaten up by seven skinny ones;

77
00:11:15,420 --> 00:11:25,460
وسبع سنبلات خضر وأخر يابسات لعلي أرجع إلى الناس لعلهم يعلمون
and seven green ears of grain and ˹seven˺ others dry, so that I may return to the people and let them know."

78
00:11:25,460 --> 00:11:36,140
٤٧ قال تزرعون سبع سنين دأبا فما حصدتم فذروه في سنبله إلا قليلا مما تأكلون
47. Joseph replied, "You will plant ˹grain˺ for seven consecutive years, leaving in the ear whatever you will harvest, except for the little you will eat.

79
00:11:36,140 --> 00:11:49,280
٤٨ ثم يأتي من بعد ذلك سبع شداد يأكل ما قدمتم لهن إلا قليلا مما تحصنون
48. Then after that will come seven years of great hardship which will consume whatever you have saved, except the little you will store ˹for seed˺.

80
00:11:49,280 --> 00:11:57,260
٤٩ ثم يأتي من بعد ذلك عام فيه يغاث الناس وفيه يعصرون
49. Then after that will come a year in which people will receive abundant rain and they will press ˹oil and wine˺."

81
00:11:57,260 --> 00:12:10,400
٥٠ وقال الملك أتوني به فلما جاءه الرسول قال ارجع إلى ربك فاسألهما بال النسوة التي قطعن أيديهن
50. The King ˹then˺ said, "Bring him to me." When the messenger came to him, Joseph said, "Go back to your master and ask him about the case of the women who cut their hands.

82
00:12:10,400 --> 00:12:14,400
إن ربي بكيدهن عليم
Surely my Lord has ˹full˺ knowledge of their cunning."

83
00:12:14,400 --> 00:12:24,260
٥١ قال ما خطبكن إذ راودتن يوسف عن نفسه قلن حاش لله ما علمنا عليه من سوء
51. The King asked ˹the women˺, "What did you get when you tried to seduce Joseph?" They replied, "Allah forbid! We know nothing indecent about him." Then the Chief Minister's wife admitted,

84
00:12:24,260 --> 00:12:34,260
قالت امرأة العزيز الآن حصحص الحق أنا راودته عن نفسه وإنه لمن الصادقين
"Now the truth has come to light. It was I who tried to seduce him, and he is surely truthful.

85
00:12:35,140 --> 00:12:44,700
٥٢ ذلك ليعلم أني لم أخنه بالغيب وأن الله لا يهدي كيد الخائنين
52. From this, Joseph should know that I did not speak dishonestly about him in his absence, for Allah certainly does not guide the scheming of the dishonest.

86
00:12:44,700 --> 00:12:58,540
٥٣ وما أبرئ نفسي إن النفس لأمارة بالسوء إلا ما رحم ربي إن ربي غفور رحيم
53. And I do not seek to free myself from blame, for indeed the soul is ever inclined to evil, except those shown mercy by my Lord. Surely my Lord is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful."

87
00:12:58,540 --> 00:13:09,540
٥٤ وقال الملك أتوني به أستخلصه لنفسي فلما كلمه قال إنك اليوم لدينا مكين أمين
54. The King said, "Bring him to me. I will employ him exclusively in my service." And when Joseph spoke to him, the King said, "Today you are highly esteemed and fully trusted by us."

88
00:13:10,400 --> 00:13:15,540
٥٥ قال جعلني على خزائن الأرض إني حفيظ عليم
55. Joseph proposed, "Put me in charge of the store-houses of the land, for I am truly reliable and adept."

89
00:13:15,540 --> 00:13:22,540
٥٦ وكذلك مكنا ليوسف في الأرض يتبوأ منها حيث يشاء
56. This is how We established Joseph in the land to settle wherever he pleased.

90
00:13:23,380 --> 00:13:26,540
نصيب برحمتنا من نشاء
We shower Our mercy on whoever We will,

91
00:13:27,440 --> 00:13:29,540
ولا نضيع أجر المحسنين
and We never discount the reward of the good-doers.

92
00:13:30,680 --> 00:13:36,540
٥٧ ولأجر الآخرة خير للذين آمنوا وكانوا يتقون
57. And the reward of the Hereafter is far better for those who are faithful and are mindful ˹of Allah˺.

93
00:13:36,540 --> 00:13:44,540
٥٨ وجاء إخوة يوسف فدخلوا عليه فعرفهم وهم له منكرون
58. And Joseph's brothers came and entered his presence. He recognized them but they were unaware of who he really was.

94
00:13:45,600 --> 00:13:52,600
٥٩ ولما جهزهم بجهازهم قال أتوني بأخ لكم من أبيكم
59. When he had provided them with their supplies, he demanded, "Bring me your brother on your father's side.

95
00:13:52,600 --> 00:13:57,540
ألا ترون أني أوف الكيل وأنا خير المنزنين
Do you not see that I give full measure and I am the best of hosts?

96
00:13:58,700 --> 00:14:03,540
٦٠ فإن لم تأتوني به فلا كيل لكم عندي ولا تقربون
60. But if you do not bring him to me ˹next time˺, I will have no grain for you, nor will you ever come close to me again."

97
00:14:03,540 --> 00:14:09,540
٦١ قالوا سنراود عنه أباه وإنا لفاعلون
61. They promised, "We will try to convince his father to let him come. We will certainly do ˹our best˺."

98
00:14:10,480 --> 00:14:16,540
٦٢ وقال لفتيانه اجعلوا بضاعتهم في رحالهم لعلهم يعرفونها
62. Joseph ordered his servants to put his brothers' money back into their saddlebags so that they would

99
00:14:17,580 --> 00:14:24,540
إذا انقلبوا إلى أهلهم لعلهم يرجعون
find it when they returned to their family and perhaps they would come back.

100
00:14:25,160 --> 00:14:31,660
٦٣ فلما رجعوا إلى أبيهم قالوا يا أبانا منع منا الكيل
63. When Joseph's brothers returned to their father, they pleaded, "O our father! We have been denied ˹further˺ supplies. So send our brother with us so that we may receive our measure,

101
00:14:31,660 --> 00:14:36,660
فأرسل معنا أخانا نكتل وإنا له لحافظون
and we will definitely watch over him."

102
00:14:37,300 --> 00:14:43,660
٦٤ قال هل آمنكم عليه إلا كما أمنتكم على أخيه من قبل
64. He responded, "Should I trust you with him as I once trusted you with his brother ˹Joseph˺? But ˹only˺ Allah is the best Protector,

103
00:14:44,260 --> 00:14:50,660
فالله خير حافظا وهو أرحم الراحمين
and He is the Most Merciful of the merciful."

104
00:14:50,660 --> 00:14:57,600
٦٥ ولما فتحوا متاعهم وجدوا بضاعتهم ردت إليهم
65. When they opened their bags, they discovered that their money had been returned to them.

105
00:14:57,600 --> 00:15:04,040
قالوا يا أبانا ما نبغي هذه بضاعتنا ردت إلينا
They argued, "O our father! What more can we ask for? Here is our money, fully returned to us. Now we can buy more food for our family.

106
00:15:04,040 --> 00:15:09,480
ونمير أهلنا ونحفظ أخانا ونزداد كيل بعير
We will watch over our brother, and obtain an extra camel-load of grain. That load can be easily secured."

107
00:15:09,480 --> 00:15:11,660
ذلك كيل يسير
When they opened their bags, they discovered that their money had been returned to them. They argued, "O our father! What more can we ask for? Here is our money, fully returned to us. Now we can buy more food for our family. We will watch over our brother, and obtain an extra camel-load of grain. That load can be easily secured."

108
00:15:11,660 --> 00:15:18,980
٦٦ قال لن أرسله معكم حتى تؤتون موثقا من الله
66. Jacob insisted, "I will not send him with you until you give me a solemn oath by Allah that you will certainly bring him back to me, unless you are totally overpowered." Then after they had given him their oaths, he concluded, "Allah

109
00:15:18,980 --> 00:15:23,440
لتأتنني به إلا أن يحاط بكم
is

110
00:15:23,440 --> 00:15:30,700
فلما آتوه موثقهم قال الله على ما نقول وكيل
a Witness to what we have said."

111
00:15:30,700 --> 00:15:35,720
٦٧ وقال يا بني لا تدخلوا من باب واحد
67. He then instructed ˹them˺, "O my sons! Do not enter ˹the city˺ all through one gate,

112
00:15:35,720 --> 00:15:39,700
وادخلوا من أبواب متفرقة
but through separate gates.

113
00:15:39,700 --> 00:15:44,940
وما أغني عنكم من الله من شيء
I cannot help you against ˹what is destined by˺ Allah in the least.

114
00:15:44,940 --> 00:15:52,720
إن الحكم إلا لله عليه توكلت وعليه فليتوكل المتوكلون
It is only Allah Who decides. In Him I put my trust. And in Him let the faithful put their trust."

115
00:15:52,720 --> 00:16:06,780
٦٨ ولما دخلوا من حيث أمرهم أبوهم ما كان يغني عنهم من الله من شيء
68. Then when they entered as their father had instructed them, this did not help them against ˹the Will of˺ Allah whatsoever.

116
00:16:06,780 --> 00:16:10,940
إلا حاجة في نفس يعقوب قضاها
It was just a desire in Jacob's heart which he satisfied.

117
00:16:10,940 --> 00:16:19,500
وإنه لذو علم لما علمناه ولكن أكثر الناس لا يعلمون
He was truly blessed with ˹great˺ knowledge because of what We had taught him, but most people have no knowledge.

118
00:16:19,500 --> 00:16:24,820
٦٩ ولما دخلوا على يوسف آوى إليه أخاه
69. When they entered Joseph's presence, he called his brother ˹Benjamin˺ aside, and confided ˹to him˺, "I am indeed your brother ˹Joseph˺!

119
00:16:24,820 --> 00:16:31,420
قال إني أنا أخوك فلا تبتئس بما كانوا يعملون
So do not feel distressed about what they have been doing."

120
00:16:31,420 --> 00:16:37,500
٧٠ فلما جهزهم بجهازهم جعل السقاية في رحل أخيه
70. When Joseph had provided them with supplies, he slipped the royal cup into his brother's bag.

121
00:16:37,500 --> 00:16:44,340
ثم أذن مؤذن أيتها العير إنكم لسارقون
Then a herald cried, "O people of the caravan! You must be thieves!"

122
00:16:44,340 --> 00:16:48,980
٧١ قالوا وأقبلوا عليهم ماذا تفقدون
71. They asked, turning back, "What have you lost?"

123
00:16:48,980 --> 00:16:57,900
٧٢ قالوا نفقد صواع الملك ولمن جاء به حمل بعير وأنا به زعيم
72. The herald ˹along with the guards˺ replied, "We have lost the King's measuring cup. And whoever brings it will be awarded a camel-load ˹of grain˺. I guarantee it."

124
00:16:57,900 --> 00:17:06,420
٧٣ قالوا تالله لقد علمتم ما جئنا لنفسد في الأرض وما كنا سارقين
73. Joseph's brothers replied, "By Allah! You know well that we did not come to cause trouble in the land, nor are we thieves."

125
00:17:06,420 --> 00:17:12,200
٧٤ قالوا فما جزاؤه إن كنتم كاذبين
74. Joseph's men asked, "What should be the price for theft, if you are lying?"

126
00:17:12,200 --> 00:17:23,120
٧٥ قالوا جزاؤه من وجد في رحله فهو جزاؤه كذلك نجزي الظالمين
75. Joseph's brothers responded, "The price will be ˹the enslavement of˺ the one in whose bag the cup is found. That is how we punish the wrongdoers."

127
00:17:23,120 --> 00:17:32,040
٧٦ فبدأ بأوعيتهم قبل وعاء أخيه ثم استخرجها من وعاء
76. Joseph began searching their bags before that of his brother ˹Benjamin˺, then brought it out of Benjamin's bag.

128
00:17:32,040 --> 00:17:39,320
أخيه كذلك كدنا ليوسف ما كان ليأخذ أخاه في دين الملك
This is how We inspired Joseph to plan. He could not have taken his brother under the King's law,

129
00:17:39,320 --> 00:17:48,240
إلا أن يشاء الله نرفع درجات من نشاء
but Allah had so willed. We elevate in rank whoever We will.

130
00:17:48,240 --> 00:17:53,240
وفوق كل ذي علم عليم
But above those ranking in knowledge is the One All-Knowing.

131
00:17:53,240 --> 00:18:03,220
٧٧ قالوا إن يسرق فقد سرق أخ له من قبل فأسرها يوسف في نفسه ولم يبدها لهم
77. ˹To distance themselves,˺ Joseph's brothers argued, "If he has stolen, so did his ˹full˺ brother before." But Joseph suppressed his outrage—revealing nothing to them—and said ˹to himself˺,

132
00:18:03,220 --> 00:18:10,120
قال أنتم شر مكانا والله أعلم بما تصفون
"You are in such an evil position, and Allah knows best ˹the truth of˺ what you claim."

133
00:18:10,120 --> 00:18:22,020
٧٨ قالوا يا أيها العزيز إن له أبا شيخا كبيرا فخذ أحدنا مكانه إنا نراك من المحسنين
78. They appealed, "O Chief Minister! He has a very old father, so take one of us instead. We surely see you as one of the good-doers."

134
00:18:22,020 --> 00:18:32,020
٧٩ قال معاذ الله أن نأخذ إلا من وجدنا متاعنا عنده إنا إذا لظالمون
79. Joseph responded, "Allah forbid that we should take other than the one with whom we found our property. Otherwise, we would surely be unjust."

135
00:18:32,620 --> 00:18:36,820
٨٠ فلما استيئسوا منه خلصوا نجيا
80. When they lost all hope in him, they spoke privately.

136
00:18:36,820 --> 00:18:51,680
قال كبيرهم ألم تعلموا أن أباكم قد أخذ عليكم موثقا من الله
The eldest of them said, "Do you not know that your father had taken a solemn oath by Allah from you, nor how you failed him regarding Joseph before? So I am not leaving this land until my father allows me to, or Allah decides for me.

137
00:18:51,680 --> 00:19:02,820
ومن قبل ما فردتم في يوسف فلن أبرح الأرض حتى يأذن لي أبي أو يحكم الله لي وهو خير الحاكمين
For He is the Best of Judges.

138
00:19:02,820 --> 00:19:17,120
٨١ ارجعوا إلى أبيكم فقولوا يا أبانا إن ابنك سرق وما شهدنا إلا بما علمنا وما كنا للغيب حافظين
81. Return to your father and say, 'O our father! Your son committed theft. We testify only to what we know. We could not guard against the unforeseen.

139
00:19:17,120 --> 00:19:26,420
٨٢ واسأل القرية التي كنا فيها والعير التي أقبلنا فيها وإنا لصادقون
82. Ask ˹the people of˺ the land where we were and the caravan we travelled with. We are certainly telling the truth.'"

140
00:19:26,420 --> 00:19:33,160
٨٣ قال بل سولت لكم أنفسكم أمرا فصبر جميل
83. He cried, "No! Your souls must have tempted you to do something ˹evil˺. So ˹I am left with nothing but˺ beautiful patience!

141
00:19:33,160 --> 00:19:41,600
عسى الله أن يأتيني بهم جميعا إنه هو العليم الحكيم
I trust Allah will return them all to me. Surely He ˹alone˺ is the All-Knowing, All-Wise."

142
00:19:41,600 --> 00:19:50,360
٨٤ وتولى عنهم وقال يا أسفى على يوسف وبيضت عيناه من الحزن فهو كظيم
84. He turned away from them, lamenting, "Alas, poor Joseph!" And his eyes turned white out of the grief he suppressed.

143
00:19:50,360 --> 00:19:58,500
٨٥ قالوا تالله تفتأ تذكر يوسف حتى تكون حرضا أو تكون من الهالكين
85. They said, "By Allah! You will not cease to remember Joseph until you lose your health or ˹even˺ your life."

144
00:19:58,500 --> 00:20:18,600
٨٦ قال إنما أشكوا بثي وحزني إلى الله وأعلم من الله ما لا تعلمون
86. He replied, "I complain of my anguish and sorrow only to Allah, and I know from Allah what you do not know.

145
00:20:18,600 --> 00:20:27,100
٨٧ يا بني يذهبوا فتحسسوا من يوسف وأخيه ولا تيأسوا من روح الله
87. O my sons! Go and search ˹diligently˺ for Joseph and his brother. And do not lose hope in the mercy of Allah,

146
00:20:27,100 --> 00:20:33,560
إنه لا ييأس من روح الله إلا القوم الكافرون
for no one loses hope in Allah's mercy except those with no faith."

147
00:20:33,560 --> 00:20:47,320
٨٨ فلما دخلوا عليه قالوا يا أيها العزيز مسلا وأهلنا الضر وجئنا ببضاعة مزجات
88. When they entered Joseph's presence, they pleaded, "O Chief Minister! We and our family have been touched with hardship, and we have brought only a few worthless coins,

148
00:20:47,320 --> 00:20:55,060
فأوفلنا الكيل وتصدق علينا إن الله يجزي المتصدقين
but ˹please˺ give us our supplies in full and be charitable to us. Indeed, Allah rewards the charitable."

149
00:20:55,060 --> 00:21:02,340
٨٩ قال هل علمتم ما فعلتم بيوسف وأخيه إذ أنتم جاهلون
89. He asked, "Do you remember what you did to Joseph and his brother in your ignorance?"

150
00:21:02,340 --> 00:21:11,500
٩٠ قالوا أئنك لأنت يوسف قال أنا يوسف وهذا أخي قد من الله علينا
90. They replied ˹in shock˺, "Are you really Joseph?" He said, "I am Joseph, and here is my brother ˹Benjamin˺! Allah has truly been gracious to us.

151
00:21:11,500 --> 00:21:19,340
إنه من يتق ويصبر فإن الله لا يضيع عجر المحسنين
Surely whoever is mindful ˹of Allah˺ and patient, then certainly Allah never discounts the reward of the good-doers."

152
00:21:19,340 --> 00:21:26,560
٩١ قالوا تالله لقد آثرك الله علينا وإن كنا لخاطئين
91. They admitted, "By Allah! Allah has truly preferred you over us, and we have surely been sinful."

153
00:21:26,560 --> 00:21:34,620
٩٢ قال لا تثريب عليكم اليوم يغفر الله لكم وهو أرحم الراحمين
92. Joseph said, "There is no blame on you today. May Allah forgive you! He is the Most Merciful of the merciful!

154
00:21:34,620 --> 00:21:41,560
٩٣ اذهبوا بقميصي هذا فألقوه على وجه أبي يأتي بصيرا
93. Go with this shirt of mine and cast it over my father's face, and he will regain his sight.

155
00:21:41,560 --> 00:21:47,560
يأتي بصيرا وأتوني بأهلكم أجمعين
Then come back to me with your whole family."

156
00:21:47,560 --> 00:21:58,020
٩٤ ولما فصلت العير قال أبوهم إني لأجد ريح يوسف لولا أن تفندون
94. When the caravan departed ˹from Egypt˺, their father said ˹to those around him˺, "You may think I am senile, but I certainly sense the smell of Joseph."

157
00:21:58,020 --> 00:22:02,560
٩٥ قالوا تالله إنك لفي طلالك القديم
95. They replied, "By Allah! You are definitely still in your old delusion."

158
00:22:02,560 --> 00:22:10,900
٩٦ فلما أن جاء البشير ألقاه على وجهه فارتد بصيرا
96. But when the bearer of the good news arrived, he cast the shirt over Jacob's face, so he regained his sight.

159
00:22:10,900 --> 00:22:17,560
قال ألم أقل لكم إني أعلم من الله ما لا تعلمون
Jacob then said ˹to his children˺, "Did I not tell you that I truly know from Allah what you do not know?"

160
00:22:18,100 --> 00:22:24,560
٩٧ قالوا يا أبان استغفر لنا ذنوبنا إنا كنا خاطئين
97. They begged, "O our father! Pray for the forgiveness of our sins. We have certainly been sinful."

161
00:22:24,560 --> 00:22:32,560
٩٨ قال سوف أستغفر لكم ربي إنه هو الغفور الرحيم
98. He said, "I will pray to my Lord for your forgiveness. He ˹alone˺ is indeed the All-Forgiving, Most Merciful."

162
00:22:33,140 --> 00:22:43,560
٩٩ فلما دخلوا على يوسف آوى إليه أبويه وقال دخلوا مصر إن شاء الله آمنين
99. When they entered Joseph's presence, he received his parents ˹graciously˺ and said, "Enter Egypt, Allah willing, in security."

163
00:22:43,560 --> 00:22:48,560
١٠٠ ورفع أبويه على العرش وخروا له سجدا
100. Then he raised his parents to the throne, and they all fell down in prostration to Joseph,

164
00:22:49,440 --> 00:22:56,560
وقال يا أبت هذا تأويل رؤياي من قبل قد جعلها ربي حقا
who then said, "O my dear father! This is the interpretation of my old dream. My Lord has made it come true.

165
00:22:57,280 --> 00:23:06,560
وقد أحسن بي إذ أخرجني من السجن وجاء بكم من البدو من بعد أن نزغ الشيطان
He was truly kind to me when He freed me from prison, and brought you all from the desert after Satan had ignited rivalry between me and my siblings.

166
00:23:06,560 --> 00:23:20,560
من بعد أن نزغ الشيطان بيني وبين إخوتي إن ربي لطيف لما يشاء إنه هو العليم الحكيم
and brought you all from the desert after Satan had ignited rivalry between me and my siblings. Indeed my Lord is subtle in fulfilling what He wills. Surely He ˹alone˺ is the All-Knowing, All-Wise."

167
00:23:21,580 --> 00:23:28,560
١٠١ ربي قد آتيتني من الملك وعلمتني من تأويل الأحاديث
101. "My Lord! You have surely granted me authority and taught me the interpretation of dreams. ˹O˺ Originator of the heavens and the earth!

168
00:23:28,560 --> 00:23:35,560
فاطر السماوات والأرض أنت ولي في الدنيا والآخرة
You are my Guardian in this world and the Hereafter.

169
00:23:36,240 --> 00:23:39,560
أنت ولي في الدنيا والآخرة
You are my Guardian in this world and the Hereafter.

170
00:23:40,340 --> 00:23:44,560
توفني مسلما وألحقني بالصالحين
Allow me to die as one who submits and join me with the righteous."

171
00:23:45,680 --> 00:23:50,560
١٠٢ ذلك من أنباء الغيب نوحيه إليك
102. That is from the stories of the unseen which We reveal to you ˹O Prophet˺.

172
00:23:51,360 --> 00:23:56,560
وما كنت لديهم إذ أجمعوا أمرهم وهم يمكرون
You were not present when they ˹all˺ made up their minds, and when they plotted ˹against Joseph˺.

173
00:23:56,560 --> 00:24:02,820
١٠٣ وما أكثر الناس ولو حرصت بمؤمنين
103. And most people will not believe—no matter how keen you are—

174
00:24:02,820 --> 00:24:08,560
١٠٤ وما تسألهم عليه من أجر إنه إلا ذكر للعالمين
104. even though you are not asking them for a reward for this ˹Quran˺. It is only a reminder to the whole world.

175
00:24:09,340 --> 00:24:17,560
١٠٥ وكأي من آية في السماوات والأرض يمرون عليها وهم عنها معرضون
105. How many signs in the heavens and the earth do they pass by with indifference!

176
00:24:18,240 --> 00:24:23,960
١٠٦ وما يؤمن أكثرهم بالله إلا وهم مشركون
106. And most of them do not believe in Allah without associating others with Him ˹in worship˺.

177
00:24:23,960 --> 00:24:29,300
١٠٧ أفأمنوا أن تأتيهم راشية من عذاب الله
107. Do they feel secure that an overwhelming torment from Allah will not overtake them,

178
00:24:29,300 --> 00:24:33,960
أو تأتيهم الساعة بغتة وهم لا يشعرون
or that the Hour will not take them by surprise when they least expect ˹it˺?

179
00:24:33,960 --> 00:24:41,420
١٠٨ قل هذه سبيلي أدعو إلى الله على بصيرة أنا ومن اتبعني
108. Say, ˹O Prophet,˺ "This is my way. I invite to Allah with insight—I and those who follow me.

180
00:24:41,420 --> 00:24:58,120
وسبحان الله وسبحان الله وما أنا من المشركين
I invite to Allah with insight—I and those who follow me. Glory be to Allah, and I am not one of the polytheists."

181
00:24:58,120 --> 00:25:06,820
١٠٩ وما أرسلنا من قبلك إلا رجالا نوحي إليهم من أهل القرى
109. We only sent before you ˹O Prophet˺ men inspired by Us from among the people of each society.

182
00:25:06,820 --> 00:25:13,460
أفلم يسيروا في الأرض فينظروا كيف كان عاقبة الذين من قبلهم
Have the deniers not travelled through the land to see what was the end of those ˹destroyed˺ before them? And surely the ˹eternal˺ Home of the Hereafter

183
00:25:13,460 --> 00:25:19,460
ولدار الآخرة خير للذين اتقوا أفلا تعقلون
is far better for those mindful ˹of Allah˺. Will you not then understand?

184
00:25:19,460 --> 00:25:26,800
١١٠ حتى إذا استيأس الرسل وظنوا أنهم قد كذبوا
110. And when the messengers despaired and their people thought the messengers had been denied help,

185
00:25:26,800 --> 00:25:29,460
جاءهم نصرنا
Our help came to them ˹at last˺.

186
00:25:29,460 --> 00:25:34,460
جاءهم نصرنا فنجي من نشاء
Our help came to them ˹at last˺. We then saved whoever We willed,

187
00:25:35,300 --> 00:25:39,460
ولا يرد بأسنا عن القوم المجرمين
and Our punishment is never averted from the wicked people.

188
00:25:39,460 --> 00:25:45,780
١١١ لقد كان في قصصهم عبرة لأولي الألباب
111. In their stories there is truly a lesson for people of reason.

189
00:25:45,780 --> 00:25:49,320
ما كان حديثا يفترى
This message cannot be a fabrication,

190
00:25:49,320 --> 00:25:53,400
ولكن تصديق الذي بين يديه
rather ˹it is˺ a confirmation of previous revelation,

191
00:25:53,400 --> 00:26:01,560
وتفصيل كل شيء وهدى ورحمة لقوم يؤمنون
a detailed explanation of all things, a guide, and a mercy for people of faith.
